                <h3>SUMMARY</h3>
                <h4 class="program">The goal was to i) establish a program for identifying high performing employees with leadership potential within a company and ii) identify how to best train them for leadership positions. Specifically, my thesis concentrated on how a firm can gain a competitive advantage by identifying and supporting potential leaders within a company more effectively than their competitors with a high potential employee program. Though the thesis was done in partnership with the head of HR at Rovio, a global video game and consumer products company, the fundamentals, foundation, and service design processes behind this program are applicable virtually in any company</h4>
                <h3>PROBLEM STATEMENT</h3>
                <h4>Identifying and training high potential employees or recruiting them is expensive and time consuming. As a result, the goal of this program is to give firms the best return on the investment possible by identifying the most effective leadership identification and training practices</h4>
